onCreate.name: onCreate
onCreate.description: Callback called when script is loaded

onDestroy.name: onDestroy
onDestroy.description: Callback called when script is closed

removeEvent.name: removeEvent
removeEvent.description: Receives a named event with a json object

shareImage.name: shareImage
shareImage.description: Share Image with an app installed in the system

onPause.name: onPause
onPause.description: Callback called when script is paused. For example when switching to a different task.

onResume.name: onResume
onResume.description: Callback called when script is resumed. This can be called either when the app loads for the first time or switches back from a different app.

liveCodingOverlay.name: liveCodingOverlay
liveCodingOverlay.description: Shows a feedback overlay with the live-executed code

runOnUiThread.name: runOnUiThread
runOnUiThread.description: Runs a function in the UI thread. This is normally not needed but might be required when combined with Threads

eval.name: eval
eval.description:
Runs a string of Javascript code
 Don't abuse this!

load.name: load
load.description: Loads and external file containing code

shareText.name: shareText
shareText.description: Share text with an app installed in the system

sendEvent.name: sendEvent
sendEvent.description: Sends a name event with a json object

openFileWithApp.name: openFileWithApp
openFileWithApp.description: Try to open a file with an app installed in the system

listenEvent.name: listenEvent
listenEvent.description: Receives a named event with a json object

log.name: log
log.description: Shows any text in the WebIDE console

error.name: error
error.description: Shows any text in the WebIDE console

addTitle.name: addTitle
addTitle.description: Adds an overlay title to the script

allowScroll.name: allowScroll
allowScroll.description:
Allows the main interface to scroll up and down.
 It's quite handy to lay out many widgets that cannot fit in a screen.

addSubtitle.name: addSubtitle
addSubtitle.description: Adds an overlay subtitle to the script

addMatrix.name: addMatrix
addMatrix.description: Adds a matrix with M and N size. Useful when creating step sequencers and similar.

addTextArea.name: addTextArea
addTextArea.description: Add a text area (which is the same as an input but multiline

addMap.name: addMap
addMap.description: Adds a map widget using OpenStreetMap

removeAllViews.name: removeAllViews
removeAllViews.description: Remove all views in the layout

addPager.name: addPager
addPager.description: Creates a pager that contain slidable views

add.name: add
add.description: Adds a view created with newView

addProcessingCanvas.name: addProcessingCanvas
addProcessingCanvas.description:
Adds a processing view. This Processing view acts quite similar to Processing.org for Android. In fact it is the same, although some things work a bit differently to play well with the rest of the framework.

- All the Processing functions prepend the Processing (p) object. p.fill(255); p.stroke(); p.rect();

positionMode.name: positionMode
positionMode.description:
Changes the position cornerMode.
 By default, Phonk places the widgets using normalized coordinates (0 to 1)
 Sometimes we need a bit more control on how to create layouts so we can specify that the
 views will lay out using pixel or dp (density independent pixels) units

addPlot.name: addPlot
addPlot.description: Adds a plot, by default the range is [0, 1]

showWeb.name: showWeb
showWeb.description:
Shows a web in a different screen.
 Once the web is opened, we loose the control of the script

takeViewScreenshot.name: takeViewScreenshot
takeViewScreenshot.description: Takes a screenshot of a view in a Bitmap form

background.name: background
background.description: Changes the background color using Hexadecimal color

resize.name: resize
resize.description: Resize a view to a given width and height. If a parameter is -1 then that dimension is not changed

addSlider.name: addSlider
addSlider.description: Adds a slider. By default the range is [0, 1].

onKeyDown.name: onKeyDown
onKeyDown.description: Tells which software / hardware / gamepad button is pressed

listInstalledApps.name: listInstalledApps
listInstalledApps.description: Loads the list of installed applications in mApplications.

battery.name: battery
battery.description: Get the current device battery level

onSmsReceived.name: onSmsReceived
onSmsReceived.description: This method will be triggered when an SMS is received

onNewNotification.name: onNewNotification
onNewNotification.description:
Gets notifications from other apps.
 In order to work to must enable the access of notifications in your device settings

openWebSearch.name: openWebSearch
openWebSearch.description: Open the search app with the given text

copyToClipboard.name: copyToClipboard
copyToClipboard.description: Copy a given text into the clipboard.

isScreenOn.name: isScreenOn
isScreenOn.description: Check if the screen is on

isAirplaneMode.name: isAirplaneMode
isAirplaneMode.description: Check if the device is in airplane cornerMode

wakeLock.name: wakeLock
wakeLock.description: Prevent the device suspend at any time. Good for long living operations

openEmailApp.name: openEmailApp
openEmailApp.description:
Creates a new mail using the default e-mail app.
 Note: It won't be automatically send

onKeyUp.name: onKeyUp
onKeyUp.description: Tells which software / hardware / gamepad button is released

openWebApp.name: openWebApp
openWebApp.description: Open the default web browser with a given Url

smsSend.name: smsSend
smsSend.description:
Sends a SMS to a given phone number.
 Please, be careful, since this method might cost you MONEY depending on your phone plan!

call.name: call
call.description: Call a given phone number using the device's call manager

onKeyEvent.name: onKeyEvent
onKeyEvent.description: Gives a key event when of a software / hardware / gamepad button

getFromClipboard.name: getFromClipboard
getFromClipboard.description: Get the content from the clipboard

openDial.name: openDial
openDial.description: Open the system's phone dial screen

pixelsToGeo.name: pixelsToGeo
pixelsToGeo.description: Get coordinates from the pixel position of the map

mapBoxTileSource.name: mapBoxTileSource
mapBoxTileSource.description: Set a new tile source such as mapbox and others

multitouch.name: multitouch
multitouch.description: Enable/Disable the multitouch events in the map

center.name: center
center.description: Gets the current center of the map

zoom.name: zoom
zoom.description: Gets the current zoom of the map

tileSource.name: tileSource
tileSource.description: Set a new tile source such as mapbox and others

removePath.name: removePath
removePath.description: Removes a path from the map

geoToPixels.name: geoToPixels
geoToPixels.description: Get coordinates from the pixel position of the map

createPath.name: createPath
createPath.description:
Creates a path in which it can be added new point
 Once the path is created, we can add points to it

addMarker.name: addMarker
addMarker.description:
Add a marker to the map.
 The params object accepts params as follows
 {
 lon: 21.1,
 lat: 22.2,
 icon: "myicon.png",
 title: "hello",
 description: "Bubble info"
 }
